'''瓦龙'''（{{bd|1986年}}，{{lang-my|ဝလုံး}}），[[路透社|路透社]]缅甸特约记者，2017年12月12日，觉梭与同事[[觉梭|觉梭]]因揭露[[因丁大屠杀|因丁大屠杀]]真相被当局诱捕。案件旋即获国际社会关注，两人于2018年获得多个国际奖项，包括《[[时代杂志|时代杂志]]》2018年[[時代年度風雲人物|年度风云人物]]、2019年[[联合国教科文组织吉列尔莫·卡诺世界新闻自由奖|联合国教科文组织吉列尔莫·卡诺世界新闻自由奖]]、[[普利策国际报道奖|普利策国际报道奖]]，同时也一直是[[国际特赦组织|国际特赦组织]]、[[美国笔会|美国笔会]]和[[无国界记者|无国界记者]]等人权组织声援的对象。

2019年5月7日，两人获总统特赦。

== 早年 ==
瓦龙生于缅甸[[曼德勒|曼德勒]]北部[[瑞波县|瑞波县]]金比村的一个水稻种植户家庭<ref name="Kermeliotis"/>。2004年前后，来到[[毛淡棉|毛淡棉]]投靠身为僧侣的叔叔，负责寺庙的清洁及饮食<ref name="booklovers">{{cite news |last1=Slodkowski |first1=Antoni |last2=Naing |first2=Shoon |last3=Aung |first3=Thu Thu |title=Arrested Myanmar reporters: Two book lovers dedicated to their craft |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-myanmar-journalists-profiles/arrested-myanmar-reporters-two-book-lovers-dedicated-to-the-truth-idUSKBN1ED0J8 |accessdate=2018-12-25 |work=Reuters |date=2017-12-19 |archive-date=2021-01-03 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210103141221/https://www.reuters.com/article/us-myanmar-journalists-profiles/arrested-myanmar-reporters-two-book-lovers-dedicated-to-the-truth-idUSKBN1ED0J8 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。2010年与哥哥到[[仰光|仰光]]开照相馆<ref name="booklovers"/>，也活跃于志愿服务及慈善事业<ref name="Kermeliotis"/>。

其后担任《人民时代》周报等地方报社的记者<ref name="booklovers"/><ref name="HuffPost">{{cite web |title=Wa Lone Journalist and photographer |url=https://www.huffingtonpost.com/author/wa-lone |website=HuffPost |accessdate=2018-12-26 |archive-date=2021-01-03 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210103141226/https://www.huffpost.com/author/wa-lone |dead-url=no }}</ref>，2014年加入《{{tsl|en|Myanmar Times|缅甸时报}}》，2016年进入[[路透社|路透社]]<ref name="Kermeliotis"/>。长期报道军政府治下缅甸的内部冲突，也报道了2015年[[诺贝尔和平奖|诺贝尔和平奖]]得主[[昂山素季|昂山素季]]历史性参与选举，2017年报道知名政治人物[[哥尼|哥尼]]遇害案<ref name="PEN2018"/>。2017年，瓦龙和觉梭报道上千名罗兴亚难民在军方镇压后，从缅甸逃往孟加拉<ref name="Vick"/>。

== 被捕 ==
=== 因丁大屠杀报道 ===
{{further|因丁大屠杀}}

2017年8月下旬，位于若开邦因丁村的罗兴亚人村庄遭纵火，大批村民逃亡山中躲避。9月1日，10名前往海滩寻找食物罗兴亚族男子被全副武装的士兵和准军方人员扣押，次日遭射杀，埋于[[萬人塚|万人坑]]<ref>{{cite news|last1=Lone|first1=Wa|last2=Oo|first2=Kyaw Soe|last3=Lewis|first3=Simon|last4=Slodkowski|first4=Antoni|title=Massacre in Myanmar: One grave for 10 Rohingya men|url=https://www.reuters.com/investigates/special-report/myanmar-rakhine-events/|accessdate=2018-02-10|work=Reuters|archive-date=2018-02-09|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180209210907/https://www.reuters.com/investigates/special-report/myanmar-rakhine-events/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。觉梭和瓦龙之后前往因丁调查万人坑，采访佛教徒村民及安全人员，获得屠杀事件的证词及照片证据<ref name="Hughes">{{cite news |last1=Hughes |first1=Roland |title=Myanmar Rohingya: How a 'genocide' was investigated |url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-45341112 |accessdate=2019-05-11 |work=BBC News |date=2018-09-03 |archive-date=2018-10-19 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181019205617/https://www.bbc.com/news/world-45341112 |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name="BBC">{{cite news |title=Pair who reported on massacre to be tried |url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-asia-44762425 |accessdate=2018-07-09 |work=BBC News |date=2018-07-09 |archive-date=2021-01-03 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210103141308/https://www.bbc.com/news/world-asia-44762425 |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Reuters reporters to face Myanmar trial for 'breach' of secrecy act |url=https://www.scmp.com/news/asia/southeast-asia/article/2154377/reuters-reporters-face-myanmar-trial-breach-secrecy-act |accessdate=2018-07-09 |work=South China Morning Post |date=2018-07-09 |archive-date=2021-01-03 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210103141227/https://www.scmp.com/news/asia/southeast-asia/article/2154377/reuters-reporters-face-myanmar-trial-breach-secrecy-act |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

=== 警方行动 ===
2017年12月12日，{{tsl|en|Myanmar Police Force|缅甸警察}}邀请觉梭和瓦龙到[[仰光|仰光]]一家餐厅吃晚饭，趁机两人<ref name="Rezaian">{{cite news|last1=Rezaian|first1=Jason|title=These journalists were jailed for investigating atrocities in Burma. This is what they found.|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/worldviews/wp/2018/02/09/these-journalists-were-jailed-for-investigating-atrocities-in-burma-this-is-what-they-found/|accessdate=2018-02-10|work=The Washington Post|date=2018-02-09|archive-date=2018-07-09|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180709134019/https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/worldviews/wp/2018/02/09/these-journalists-were-jailed-for-investigating-atrocities-in-burma-this-is-what-they-found/|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="PEN2018">{{cite news |title=Wa Lone and Kyaw Soe Oo |url=https://pen.org/advocacy-case/wa-lone-kyaw-soe-oo/ |accessdate=2018-12-26 |work=PEN America |date=2018 |archive-date=2021-01-03 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210103141228/https://pen.org/advocacy-case/wa-lone-kyaw-soe-oo/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>。据两人后来亿述，当时他们向警察展示了对方从未见过的文件，旋即遭到逮捕。警方在召开记者会时，未提及餐厅的事情，声称两位记者在仰光郊区被捕<ref name="Myanmar">{{cite news|title=Myanmar policeman who arrested Reuters reporters tells court he burned|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-myanmar-journalists/myanmar-policeman-who-arrested-reuters-reporters-tells-court-he-burned-his-notes-idUSKBN1FP2W9|accessdate=2018-02-10|agency=Reuters|date=2018-02-06|archive-date=2021-01-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210103141230/https://www.reuters.com/article/us-myanmar-journalists/myanmar-policeman-who-arrested-reuters-reporters-tells-court-he-burned-his-notes-idUSKBN1FP2W9|dead-url=no}}</ref>。两人被控违反[[英属缅甸|殖民地时期]]的《官方保密法》中有关持有机密文件的规定，若被定罪将可能面临14年监禁<ref name="Rohingya">{{cite news|title=Reuters: Journalists held for probing Rohingya massacre|url=http://www.aljazeera.com/news/2018/02/reuters-journalists-held-probing-rohingya-massacre-180209055511736.html|accessdate=2018-02-10|work=Al Jazeera|archive-date=2021-01-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210103141231/https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2018/2/9/reuters-journalists-held-for-probing-rohingya-massacre|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

路透社其后发表声明，表示两人被捕前曾前去调查在因丁村发现的万人坑，要求当局立即释放两人。2018年2月8日两人案件的最后一场听证会结束后，路透社公布了两人调查发现的所有证据<ref name="Massacre">{{cite news|title=Reuters Publishes Story Of Myanmar Massacre After 2 Journalists Arrested|url=https://www.npr.org/sections/thetwo-way/2018/02/09/584480378/reuters-publishes-story-of-myanmar-massacre-after-2-journalists-arrested|accessdate=2018-02-10|work=NPR|archive-date=2021-01-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210103141330/https://www.npr.org/sections/thetwo-way/2018/02/09/584480378/reuters-publishes-story-of-myanmar-massacre-after-2-journalists-arrested|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="Details">{{cite news|title=Reuters Report Details Work of Journalists Detained in Myanmar|url=https://www.voanews.com/a/reuters-report-details-work-journalists-detained-myanmar/4246987.html|accessdate=2018-02-10|work=VOA|archive-date=2021-01-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210103141254/https://www.voanews.com/east-asia-pacific/reuters-report-details-work-journalists-detained-myanmar|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

===诱捕===
[[File:Myanmar_Police_outside_Insein_Township_courtroom_(Aung_Naing_Soe-VOA).jpg|thumb]]
两名记者被捕当天，缅甸警察队长莫扬南因违反《警察纪律法》被捕。4月20日的首场聆讯中，莫扬南作为检方传唤的目击证人出庭作证。据他透露，上级命令他和一名同事安排两位记者在餐厅见面，向他们提供所谓的“机密文件”，籍此[[钓鱼执法|诱捕]]两人<ref name="Testifies">{{cite news|title=Myanmar Policeman Testifies Arrested Reporters Were Set Up|url=https://www.voanews.com/a/myanmar-policeman-testifies-arrested-reporters-were-set-up/4358822.html|accessdate=2018-04-21|work=VOA, Associated Press|date=2018-04-20|archive-date=2021-01-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210103141325/https://www.voanews.com/east-asia-pacific/myanmar-policeman-testifies-arrested-reporters-were-set|dead-url=no}}</ref>。这位上级还威胁两人，说不听命令就会被关监狱<ref name="set"/>。

警方发言人后来认为莫扬南的发言受个人情绪影响，所作证词不足以采信<ref name="set">{{cite news|last1=Naing|first1=Shoon|title=Myanmar police 'set up' Reuters reporters in sting-police witness|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-myanmar-journalists/myanmar-police-set-up-reuters-reporters-in-sting-police-witness-idUSKBN1HR12Q|accessdate=2018-04-21|work=Reuters|date=2018-04-20|archive-date=2021-01-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210103141305/https://www.reuters.com/article/us-myanmar-journalists/myanmar-police-set-up-reuters-reporters-in-sting-police-witness-idUSKBN1HR12Q|dead-url=no}}</ref>。4月21日，莫扬南的家人被驱逐出警方宿舍<ref name="Thu">{{cite news|last1=Naing|first1=Shoon|last2=Aung|first2=Thu Thu|title=Family of Myanmar policeman who described sting on Reuters...|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-myanmar-journalists/family-of-myanmar-policeman-who-described-sting-on-reuters-reporters-evicted-family-idUSKBN1HS0FQ|accessdate=2018-04-29|work=Reuters|archive-date=2021-01-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210103141256/https://www.reuters.com/article/us-myanmar-journalists/family-of-myanmar-policeman-who-described-sting-on-reuters-reporters-evicted-family-idUSKBN1HS0FQ|dead-url=no}}</ref>。4月29日，莫扬南因被反《警察纪律法》获刑1年<ref name="Han">{{cite news|last1=Han|first1=Naw Betty|title=Whistle-blower police officer gets one-year jail sentence|url=https://www.mmtimes.com/news/whistle-blower-police-officer-gets-one-year-jail-sentence.html|accessdate=2018-05-02|work=The Myanmar Times|archive-date=2018-06-26|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180626083037/https://www.mmtimes.com/news/whistle-blower-police-officer-gets-one-year-jail-sentence.html|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="South">{{cite news|title=Whistle-blowing Myanmar policeman jailed for a year|url=http://www.scmp.com/news/asia/southeast-asia/article/2144037/whistle-blowing-myanmar-policeman-jailed-year|accessdate=2018-05-02|work=South China Morning Post|agency=AFP|archive-date=2021-01-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210103141303/https://www.scmp.com/news/asia/southeast-asia/article/2144037/whistle-blowing-myanmar-policeman-jailed-year|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="Globe">{{cite news|title=Officer in Reuters reporters' case gets prison: Myanmar police|url=https://www.theglobeandmail.com/world/video-officer-in-reuters-reporters-case-gets-prison-myanmar-police/|accessdate=2018-05-02|work=The Globe and Mail|date=2018-04-30|archive-date=2018-05-02|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180502075838/https://www.theglobeandmail.com/world/video-officer-in-reuters-reporters-case-gets-prison-myanmar-police/|dead-url=yes}}</ref>。

2018年5月2日，法官裁定莫扬南证词可信，要求检方将他归类为不利证人<ref name="Lee">{{cite news|last1=Naing|first1=Shoon|last2=Lee|first2=Yimou|title=Myanmar court accepts testimony of policeman who said Reuters...|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-myanmar-journalists/myanmar-court-accepts-testimony-of-policeman-who-said-reuters-reporters-framed-idUSKBN1I30XI|accessdate=2018-05-03|agency=Reuters|date=2018-05-02|archive-date=2021-01-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210103141238/https://www.reuters.com/article/us-myanmar-journalists/myanmar-court-accepts-testimony-of-policeman-who-said-reuters-reporters-framed-idUSKBN1I30XI|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="Olarn">{{cite news|last1=Olarn|first1=Kocha|last2=Griffiths|first2=James|title=Key witness allowed to testify in trial of Reuters journalists|url=https://www.cnn.com/2018/05/02/asia/myanmar-reuters-journalists-trial-intl/index.html|accessdate=2018-05-02|publisher=CNN|date=2018-05-02|archive-date=2021-01-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210103141332/https://www.cnn.com/2018/05/02/asia/myanmar-reuters-journalists-trial-intl/index.html|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="Mon">{{cite news|last1=Mon|first1=Su Myat|title=Judge in Reuters case rejects ‘hostile witness’ claim|url=https://frontiermyanmar.net/en/judge-in-reuters-case-rejects-hostile-witness-claim|accessdate=2018-05-03|work=Frontier Myanmar|date=2018-05-02|archive-date=2018-06-26|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180626164032/https://frontiermyanmar.net/en/judge-in-reuters-case-rejects-hostile-witness-claim|dead-url=no}}</ref>。一周后的5月9日，莫扬南按要求继续在庭上作证，指警察准将钦郭郭策划了整个诱捕行动，又指对方威胁他和同事，说如果不能“把瓦龙抓回来”，就会抓他们。在证词中，莫扬南告诉监督司法程序的法官：“我知道警察准将钦郭郭指使警察准下士南林把我们在前线活动的文件给瓦龙，以此逮捕他<ref name="Shoon"/>。”警方发言人后来表示准将钦郭郭“没有理由做这样的事情”<ref name="Shoon">{{cite news|last1=Naing|first1=Shoon|last2=Aung|first2=Thu Thu|title=Myanmar policeman who said Reuters reporters were framed details...|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-myanmar-journalists/myanmar-policeman-who-said-reuters-reporters-were-framed-details-sting-operation-idUSKBN1IA1SG|accessdate=2018-05-10|agency=Reuters|date=2018-05-09|archive-date=2021-01-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210103141309/https://www.reuters.com/article/us-myanmar-journalists/myanmar-policeman-who-said-reuters-reporters-were-framed-details-sting-operation-idUSKBN1IA1SG|dead-url=no}}</ref>，准下士南林也否认自己有收到这样的命令<ref name="Naing">{{cite news|last1=Naing|first1=Shoon|last2=Aung|first2=Thu Thu|title=Myanmar policeman denies planting documents on Reuters reporters|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-myanmar-journalists/myanmar-policeman-denies-planting-documents-on-reuters-reporters-idUSKCN1IH1SQ?il=0|accessdate=2018-05-17|work=U.S.|date=2018-05-16|archive-date=2021-01-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210103141239/https://www.reuters.com/article/us-myanmar-journalists/myanmar-policeman-denies-planting-documents-on-reuters-reporters-idUSKCN1IH1SQ?il=0|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

=== 庭审 ===
2018年7月9日，经过六个月的初步聆讯，法庭正式指控两名记者获取机密国家文件，违反《官方机密法》，将案件移交审判<ref name="Act">{{cite news |title=Myanmar charges Reuters reporters under Official Secrets Act |url=https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2018/07/myanmar-charges-reuters-reporters-official-secrets-act-180709042144322.html |accessdate=2018-07-09 |work=Al Jazeera |date=2018-07-09 |archive-date=2021-01-03 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210103141308/https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2018/7/9/myanmar-charges-reuters-reporters-under-official-secrets-act |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name="BBC" /><ref name="breach">{{cite news |title=Reuters reporters to face Myanmar trial for ‘breach’ of secrecy act |url=https://www.scmp.com/news/asia/southeast-asia/article/2154377/reuters-reporters-face-myanmar-trial-breach-secrecy-act |accessdate=2018-07-09 |work=South China Morning Post |date=2018-07-09 |archive-date=2021-01-03 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210103141241/https://www.scmp.com/news/asia/southeast-asia/article/2154377/reuters-reporters-face-myanmar-trial-breach-secrecy-act |dead-url=no }}</ref>。两人表示不认罪，发誓作证，以此证明自己的无辜<ref name="Slodkowski">{{cite news |last1=Slodkowski |first1=Antoni |last2=Naing |first2=Shoon |title=Myanmar court presses secrets act charges against Reuters reporters |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-myanmar-journalists-ruling/myanmar-court-presses-secrets-act-charges-against-reuters-reporters-idUSKBN1JZ095 |accessdate=2018-07-09 |work=Reuters |date=2018-07-09 |archive-date=2021-01-03 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210103141258/https://www.reuters.com/article/us-myanmar-journalists-ruling/myanmar-court-presses-secrets-act-charges-against-reuters-reporters-idUSKBN1JZ095 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

9月3日，法庭裁定两名记者罪名成立，判刑7年<ref name="Sentence">{{cite news |last1=Barron |first1=Laignee |title=Myanmar Sentences 2 Reuters Reporters 7 Years in Prison |url=http://time.com/5375545/myanmar-reuters-reporters-convicted/ |accessdate=2018-09-03 |work=TIME |date=2018-09-03 |archive-date=2021-01-03 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210103141315/https://time.com/5375545/myanmar-reuters-reporters-convicted/ |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name="Mahtani">{{cite news |last1=Mahtani |first1=Shibani |last2=Lynn |first2=Kyaw Ye |title=Myanmar judge sentences Reuters journalists to 7 years in prison |url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/world/myanmar-judge-sentences-reuters-journalists-to-7-years-in-prison/2018/09/03/53b89674-af27-11e8-a810-4d6b627c3d5d_story.html |accessdate=2018-09-03 |work=The Washington Post |date=2018-09-03 |archive-date=2021-01-03 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210103141324/https://www.washingtonpost.com/world/myanmar-judge-sentences-reuters-journalists-to-7-years-in-prison/2018/09/03/53b89674-af27-11e8-a810-4d6b627c3d5d_story.html |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name="Fullerton">{{cite news |last1=Fullerton |first1=Jamie |last2=Goldberg |first2=Jacob |title=Reuters reporters jailed for seven years in Myanmar |url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2018/sep/03/myanmar-reuters-journalists-sentenced-to-seven-years-in-prison-rohingya |accessdate=2018-09-03 |work=The Guardian |date=2018-09-03 |archive-date=2021-01-03 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210103141243/https://www.theguardian.com/world/2018/sep/03/myanmar-reuters-journalists-sentenced-to-seven-years-in-prison-rohingya |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name="McKirdy">{{cite news |last1=McKirdy |first1=Euan |last2=Tike |first2=Ye |last3=Griffiths |first3=James |title=Myanmar: Reuters journalists investigating Rohingya killings sentenced to 7 years in prison |url=https://www.cnn.com/2018/09/03/asia/reuters-journalists-myanmar-trial-verdict-intl/index.html |accessdate=2018-09-03 |publisher=CNN |date=2018-09-03 |archive-date=2021-01-03 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210103141245/https://www.cnn.com/2018/09/03/asia/reuters-journalists-myanmar-trial-verdict-intl/index.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

=== 国际回应 ===
国际社会纷纷谴责判决结果。美国驻缅甸大使{{tsl|en|Scot Marciel|斯科特·马西尔}}认为判决结果“令人深感不安”。英国大使丹·楚格（Dan Chugg）表示英国和欧盟“极度失望”，认为法官“无视证据和缅甸的法律”<ref name="Reactions">{{cite news |title=Reactions to verdict on Reuters' Myanmar journalists |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-myanmar-journalists-reax-factbox/factbox-reactions-to-verdict-on-reuters-myanmar-journalists-idUSKCN1LJ0AJ |accessdate=2018-09-03 |agency=Reuters |date=2018-09-03 |archive-date=2021-01-03 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210103141307/https://www.reuters.com/article/us-myanmar-journalists-reax-factbox/factbox-reactions-to-verdict-on-reuters-myanmar-journalists-idUSKCN1LJ0AJ |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name="reacts">{{cite news |title=World reacts to sentencing of Reuters journalists in Myanmar |url=https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2018/09/world-reacts-sentencing-reuters-journalists-myanmar-180903052605150.html |accessdate=2018-09-03 |work=Al Jazeera |date=2018-09-03 |archive-date=2021-01-03 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210103141307/https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2018/9/3/world-reacts-to-sentencing-of-reuters-journalists-in-myanmar |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

[[国务资政_(缅甸)|国务资政]][[昂山素季|昂山素季]]为法庭判决辩护：“我们相信法治。他们拥有上诉的权利，可以指出判决结果的错误之处，如果他们认为法庭的判决是错误的<ref name="Kyi">{{cite news |title=Myanmar leader Suu Kyi defends journalists' imprisonment |url=https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2018/09/aung-san-suu-kyi-defends-imprisonment-reuters-journalists-180913053453420.html |accessdate=2018-09-13 |work=Al Jazeera |date=2018-09-13 |archive-date=2021-01-03 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210103141335/https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2018/9/13/myanmar-leader-suu-kyi-defends-journalists-imprisonment |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name="Bengali">{{cite news |last1=Bengali |first1=Shashank |title=Aung San Suu Kyi defends jailing of journalists in Myanmar: 'They have every right to appeal' |url=http://www.latimes.com/world/asia/la-fg-myanmar-suu-kyi-20180913-story.html |accessdate=2018-09-13 |work=latimes.com |date=2018-09-13 |archive-date=2021-01-03 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210103141319/https://www.latimes.com/world/asia/la-fg-myanmar-suu-kyi-20180913-story.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>。”

===上诉===
2018年11月5日，两名记者的律师发起上诉，认为法庭忽视了证明警方栽赃，严重违反正当程序可信证据，检方未能证明案中的任何关键元素。法庭没有遵照缅甸法律的规定，将举证责任从检方转移至两名记者<ref name="Ellis-Petersen">{{cite news |last1=Ellis-Petersen |first1=Hannah |title=Myanmar: imprisoned Reuters journalists launch appeal |url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2018/nov/05/myanmar-imprisoned-reuters-journalists-launch-appeal |accessdate=2018-11-05 |work=The Guardian |date=2018-11-05 |archive-date=2021-01-03 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210103141318/https://www.theguardian.com/world/2018/nov/05/myanmar-imprisoned-reuters-journalists-launch-appeal |dead-url=no }}</ref>。上诉庭审原计划于12月24日举行<ref name="Goldberg"/>，但在1月11日被驳回<ref>{{cite news |last1=Aung |first1=Thu Thu |title=Myanmar court rejects appeal by jailed Reuters reporters |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-myanmar-journalists/myanmar-court-rejects-appeal-by-jailed-reuters-reporters-idUSKCN1P50HL |accessdate=2019-05-07 |agency=Reuters |date=2019-01-11 |archive-date=2021-01-03 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210103141313/https://www.reuters.com/article/us-myanmar-journalists/myanmar-court-rejects-appeal-by-jailed-reuters-reporters-idUSKCN1P50HL |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

2019年2月1日，记者向[[缅甸最高法院|缅甸最高法院]]上诉<ref>{{cite news |last1=Aung |first1=Thu Thu |title=Jailed Reuters journalists appeal to Myanmar's top court as rights group decries 'fear' |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-myanmar-journalists/jailed-reuters-journalists-appeal-to-myanmars-top-court-as-rights-group-decries-fear-idUSKCN1PQ3NZ |accessdate=2019-05-06 |agency=Reuters |date=2019-03-15 |archive-date=2021-01-03 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210103141247/https://www.reuters.com/article/us-myanmar-journalists/jailed-reuters-journalists-appeal-to-myanmars-top-court-as-rights-group-decries-fear-idUSKCN1PQ3NZ |dead-url=no }}</ref>。案件聆讯3月25日举行<ref>{{cite news |last1=Lewis |first1=Simon |title=Myanmar's top court hears Reuters reporters' appeal in official secrets case |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-myanmar-journalists/myanmars-top-court-hears-reuters-reporters-appeal-in-official-secrets-case-idUSKCN1R705B |accessdate=2019-05-06 |date=2019-03-25 |archive-date=2021-01-03 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210103141339/https://www.reuters.com/article/us-myanmar-journalists/myanmars-top-court-hears-reuters-reporters-appeal-in-official-secrets-case-idUSKCN1R705B |dead-url=no }}</ref>。4月23日，上诉再度被驳回<ref>{{cite news |last1=Naing |first1=Shoon |title=Myanmar's top court rejects final appeal by jailed Reuters journalists |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-myanmar-journalists/myanmars-top-court-rejects-final-appeal-by-jailed-reuters-journalists-idUSKCN1RZ06O |accessdate=2019-05-06 |agency=Reuters |date=2019-04-22 |archive-date=2021-01-03 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210103141307/https://www.reuters.com/article/us-myanmar-journalists/myanmars-top-court-rejects-final-appeal-by-jailed-reuters-journalists-idUSKCN1RZ06O |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

[[国际特赦组织|国际特赦组织]]、[[美国笔会|美国笔会]]和[[无国界记者|无国界记者]]等团体代表两名记者发出呼吁<ref name="AIUSA">{{cite web |title= Myanmar: Reuters journalists must be released |url= https://www.amnestyusa.org/press-releases/myanmar-reuters-journalists-must-be-released/ |website= Amnesty International |date= 2018-01-01 |accessdate= 2018-12-25 |archive-date= 2021-01-03 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20210103141248/https://www.amnestyusa.org/press-releases/myanmar-reuters-journalists-must-be-released/ |dead-url= no }}</ref><ref name="PEN">{{cite web |title=Sign Now: Demand the release of Reuters journalists Wa Lone and Kyaw Soe Oo |url=https://pen.org/free-wa-lone-and-kyaw-soe-oo/?mc_cid=b5ca827aa9&mc_eid=3d59c3999a |website=PEN America |accessdate=2018-12-25 |archive-date=2021-01-03 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210103141249/https://pen.org/free-wa-lone-and-kyaw-soe-oo/?mc_cid=b5ca827aa9&mc_eid=3d59c3999a |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name="Reporters Without  Borders">{{cite web |title=Free Wa Lone and Kyaw Soe Oo! |url=https://rsf.org/en/free-wa-lone-and-kyaw-soe-oo |website=Reporters Without  Borders |accessdate=2018-12-25 |archive-date=2021-01-03 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210103141312/https://rsf.org/en/free-wa-lone-and-kyaw-soe-oo |dead-url=no }}</ref>。国际特赦组织认为当局逮捕两位记者，是想平息调查军方人员在若开邦对罗兴亚人实施暴力犯罪的行动，震慑其他有同等举动的记者同行<ref name="AIUSA"/>。

